Kim Yong Nam to Visit Mongolia, Algeria and Ethiopia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, will soon pay an official good-will visit to Mongolia at the invitation of its President Nambariin Enkhbayar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He will also make similar visits to Algeria and Ethiopia.

DPRK's Abductee Interviewed  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- To Chu Ji, Korean woman who had been abducted to Japan, was interviewed by media persons at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel on Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by Korean media persons and foreign correspondents here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To said at the conference that a resident in Pukchang County, South Phyongan Province, she was lured by the words of bad people that she might be given help in living and was taken to Japan against her will where she spent three years and seven months before coming back to the homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Answering the questions put by reporters, she gave an account of how she was lured and abducted to Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In October 2003, I was lured by unidentified persons into crossing the River Tuman and going to Shenyang from where she was taken to Japan. She added that she thus fell victim to an anti-DPRK plot-breeding organization of Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Saying about what she felt while staying in Japan, she noted that the Japanese authorities enforced a very harsh policy of national discrimination and that the Japanese society was corrupt and ailing one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She went on to say: I keenly realized that the place one was born and grew up is neither one's native place nor one's motherland, but the place which takes care of one's destiny and future is the genuine cradle and homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She noted: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-DPRK organizations made up of riff-raffs in Japan are now busy with all forms of false propaganda against the DPRK and the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), raising a hue and cry over "abduction issue" and "human rights issue" etc. They demanded me to attend what they called "press conference" and "meeting" in a bid to use even me for their purpose. They attempted to use even the kindred ties between parents and their children for their political purpose. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speaking of what she felt after coming back into the care of General Kim Jong Il, she said she felt ashamed when she was warmly greeted and kindly treated by everyone she met.

July 4 Joint Statement Supported by Brazilian Party 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- The Brazilian Communist Party on July 4 posted an article titled "Great Program of Reunification Common to Korean Nation" on its Internet homepage on the occasion of the 35th anniversary of the publication of the July 4 joint statement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article notes that the July 4 joint statement fully reflects the three principles of national reunification, the great program of reunification common to the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The principles put forward by President Kim Il Sung were fully supported and hailed not only by all the Korean people but by the broad international community as soon as they were published for their validity and truth, and they are displaying enormous vitality still today, notes the article, concluding:  Korea would be certainly reunified according to the above-said principles.

President Kim Il Sung Remembered in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Remembrance meetings were held in Laos, Mongolia, Mexico and Austria and film shows in Russia, Vietnam, Indonesia and Iran from July 3 to 5 on the occasion of the 13th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the venues of the functions were famous works of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and photos showing their immortal exploits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Screened at the film shows were Korean films including "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung Meets Heads of State and Prominent Figures of Foreign Countries," "The Great Life in 1994," "For Liberation of the Country" and "Comrade Kim Il Sung Will Always Be with Humankind." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the functions noted that Kim Il Sung is the eternal sun of the Korean people and the greatest man who added shine to the 20th century. They highly praised the immortal exploits of the President who defeated two formidable imperialist enemies in one generation with his outstanding leadership ability and matchless courage and grit and has turned Korea into a socialist power of independence, self-sustenance and self-reliant defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il, driving back the challenges of the imperialist allied forces with his Songun politics, is firmly defending Korean-style socialism to which Kim Il Sung dedicated his whole life, they said, adding: The Korean people will build a great prosperous powerful nation and achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country in the near future under his wise guidance.

Mongolian Ambassador Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Janchivdorjyn Lomvo, Mongolian ambassador to the DPRK, hosted a reception on July 11 on the occasion of the 86th anniversary of the victory of the Mongolian people's revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Choe Thae Bok, chairman of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Kim Wan Su, director of the Secretariat of the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland who is chairman of the DPRK-Mongolia Friendship Parliamentary Group, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

Abolition of NSL Demanded in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Members of south Korean civic and public organizations including the People's Solidarity for Abolition of the "National Security Law" reportedly held a forum in Seoul on July 7 in demand of the abolition of the NSL. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They discussed the need to tear up the NSL and the action program for the second half of the year to get the evil law scrapped. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Branding the NSL as a Draconian law suppressing democracy, human rights and the freedom of expression of idea, they said it must be repealed on all accounts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Headquarters of Youth and Students of the South Side's Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration made public a statement on July 5. It castigated it as an anti-reunification and anti-national acts for division, war and confrontation for the   public security authorities to crack down on the reunification movement of the youth and students by brandishing the evil law in the June 15 era of independent reunification, swimming against the trend of the times&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Away with the NSL that is blocking and suppressing the unanimous desire and struggle of the people for reunification, demanded the statement, declaring: The Headquarters of Youth and Students will wage a relentless fight for the abolition of the evil law.

Kim Il Sung Lauded  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Figures of Guyana and India released statements on the occasion of the 13th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hamilton Green, mayor of Georgetown City who is leader of the Good Green Guyana, in his statement on July 3 highly praised Kim Il Sung as the great leader, who embarked upon the road of revolution at his early age, liberated the country and founded the dignified DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said that the President was an outstanding statesman who clearly indicated the way to be followed by the developing countries in the building of a new society and the struggle for national liberation and led the cause of global independence to victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An Indian lawmaker in a statement on July 6 highly praised the President as a great sage who devoted his all to the happiness of people to the last moments of his life, regarding it as his maxim to believe in the people as in Heaven. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people built a rich and powerful independent and sovereign state where the people have become its master and achieved great successes in the struggle for national reunification under the wise leadership of the President, the statement said, adding that they are now closely rallied around Kim Jong Il who is identical to the President in idea and personality.

Picture Album Introducing Songun Korea Published in China
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- A picture album "Pictures on Songun Korea, Heir to the Revolutionary Traditions of Anti-Japanese Struggle" was brought out in China on July 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The album published by the Putong Zhiyuan Trading Co. Ltd in Beijing of China contains more than 200 Korean paintings and oil-paintings on diverse themes including the greatness of the three generals of Mt. Paektu, the staunch spirit of Songun Korea, folk customs of the Korean people and the friendly feelings of the peoples of the DPRK and China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Systematically edited in chronological order in the album are fine art pieces comprehensively and profoundly dealing with the major revolutionary sites and battle sites where President Kim Il Sung spent his childhood, conducted revolutionary activities in his early years and waged the anti-Japanese armed struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Printed on the front and back covers of the album are Korean paintings "Rosy Is the Future of Korea over which the Lodestar of Mt. Paektu Is Shining" and "My Country with the Strongest National Power." Seen on its first page are Korean painting "The Kumsusan Memorial Palace, the Holy Temple of the Sun" and a preface. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preface says that the Putong Zhiyuan Trading Co. Ltd in Beijing hosted an exhibition of peculiar works done by famous painters of the DPRK in Harbin, prompted by the desire to help Chinese always remember the friendship between the peoples of China and the DPRK and let them know better about the Korean people building a great prosperous powerful nation under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean fine art exhibition on the theme of "An Exhibition of Peculiar Works Done by Famous Painters of the DPRK--Pictures on Songun Korea, Heir to the Revolutionary Traditions of the Anti-Japanese Struggle" was opened there on the same day under the co-sponsorship of the Putong Zhiyuan Trading Co. Ltd in Beijing of China and the Central Committee of the Korean Artists Union.

Population Urbanization Issue Settled in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- The fast urbanization of population in the world has raised serious socio-economic problems including difficulty in city management, destruction of ecological environment and worsening working and living conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Activities are being conducted to cope with the problem in the international arena. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The DPRK government has put forward a unique socialist principle for the formation of urban population and ways for its implementation already long ago and made a history of Juche-oriented urban construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Above all, it has built more than 95 percent of cities on a minor scale and allocated industrial productive forces rationally throughout the country, thus providing conditions for even distribution of population. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The construction of satellite cities has been carried on in a big way for the purpose of distributing industrial establishments and population in areas around large cities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The government has also paid a deep attention to reducing the distinctions between towns and the countryside, a main factor of population concentration into cities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
According to data, more than 50 million rural inhabitants flow into cities in a year around the world, which accounts for over 70 percent of the total growth of urban population. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The government has taken measures to carry out thoroughly the technical, cultural and ideological revolutions in the countryside and to strengthen in every way the working class leadership to the peasantry, assistance of industry to agriculture and support of towns to the countryside. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
And in the socialist construction it has consistently held to the basic principles on continually bringing the guidance and management for agriculture closer to the advanced level of enterprise management of industry, strengthening the links between all-people property and cooperative property and bringing steadily the cooperative property to the property of whole people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It also took epochal measures to build the county as the regional base for fully ensuring the bonds between towns and the countryside and increasing the assistance of towns to the countryside and to construct many workers' districts in different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Undertakings for improving the living standard of the peasants to suit the developing economy and culture of the nation are being carried on in a planned way.

Fascist Suppression of Patriotic Youth and Students in South Korea Denounced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Korean Student Committee made public a statement Wednesday denouncing the south Korean security authorities hell bent on the fascist suppression of patriotic youth and students including members of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wholesale repression by the south Korean security authorities is a grave challenge to a unanimous purpose and desire of the south Korean youth and students and people in general for the democracy of society and reunification of the country and an unpardonable fascist violence, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sweeping roundup of pro-reunification patriots in south Korea today patently proves that the gruesome terrorism of the fascist fanatics to dampen the climate of support to the June 15 joint declaration daily growing in south Korea and destroy the pro-reunification patriotic forces as a whole is entering an extremely dangerous stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those who should face a stern judgment of the nation in the new era of history are the anti-reunification forces which, swimming against the trend of the times, are threatening the destiny of all the fellow countrymen and standing in the way of unity and which should be removed are the legal and institutional mechanisms they are depending on. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A free reunification movement of youth and students and people cannot be ensured in south Korea as long as there still exist such fascist traitorous group as the "Grand National Party" and the "National Security Law." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities should immediately release all the patriotic youth and students and people of all social strata under arrest and scrap at once the NSL, a law against the nation and ethics, already rejected in the international arena. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We express the hope and belief that the youth and students of south Korea will wage more daringly the activities to build a new democratic society free from the NSL and the June 15 era of reunification by giving a volcanic vent to the strong mettle and inexhaustible might of the youth steadfast in justice and patriotism, the statement stressed.

Fascist Action Taken by Seoul City Police Authorities under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Some days ago, the Seoul city police authorities of south Korea arrested the director in charge of Policy of the Students Committee of the Democratic Labor Party on the charge of violating the "National Security Law (NSL)" for the mere reason that he taught his juniors the Juche idea at a university. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland released Information Bulletin No. 932 on Wednesday blasting this fascist action. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin termed the repressive action of the south Korean security authorities a fascist act of blatantly chilling the aspiration and wishes of the people and an unpardonable reckless act against reunification and nation as it is intended to stem the trend of the June 15 era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Not only the south Korean people but also the world people have expressed absolute support and sympathy with the Juche idea and the Songun policy for their validity and vitality and it has become an irresistible trend of the times to study and follow them, the bulletin noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean security authorities are openly negating the ideology and system of the dialogue partner and inciting the confrontation among fellow countrymen in the era of "By our nation itself" in which the Koreans get reconciled and go united and advance towards reunification. This is a vicious provocation and challenge to the DPRK and a grave act of overturning the foundation of the inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nothing can dampen the desire of the popular masses to follow justice and truth and live in the spirit of patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean security authorities would be well advised to properly understand the desire of the popular masses and the requirements of the times and immediately discontinue the unwarranted suppression of the followers of the great Juche idea and the Songun policy and the racket of confrontation with the DPRK.

Rodong Sinmun on Tremendous Vitality of Songun Politics 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- The Songun politics being pursued by the Workers' Party of Korea is an embodiment of the Juche-oriented theory of ideology that idea decides everything and nothing is impossible when people are motivated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Thursday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Through the Songun politics the WPK has dynamically pushed forward all fields of the revolution and construction by regarding the army as a pillar and main force for the revolution and depending on the might of the revolutionary army. The theory of ideology is embodied in its Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The army transparent in thinking alone can guarantee the victory of the revolution and display its invincible might. This is the stand and will of the WPK. Precisely for this reason, the WPK has adhered to the principle of putting main emphasis on ideology as well as arms and combining the latter with the former and pushing ahead with the revolution and construction by dint of their might. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK's Songun politics is an embodiment of the theory of ideology. This can be explained well by the fact that it considers the revolutionary soldier spirit as a powerful weapon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said spirit which was created and is now being fully displayed by the soldiers of the Korean People's Army under the Songun leadership of the WPK is the noble revolutionary spirit of the Korean People's Army the keynote of which is the spirit of devotedly defending the leader, the spirit of carrying out his instructions in a do-or-die spirit and the heroic self-sacrificing spirit. It is also a spirit of dedicating one's youth and life to the party and the revolution, the country and people. This great revolutionary spirit representing the Songun era is a source of the inexhaustible might of the WPK's Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The fact that the WPK's Songun politics is an embodiment of the theory of ideology finds a vivid expression in that it attaches decisive importance to the ideological education and gives top priority to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK is now paying deep attention to properly combining political and ideological education, moral education and education in cultural and emotional life in the ideological work as required by the Songun politics. The WPK raised the issues of educating people to have loyalty to the party and the leader as their faith, conscience, morality and part of their life and cherish patriotism not only as ideological faith but as conscience and a moral obligation. The policies for ideological education put forward by the WPK are displaying their tremendous vitality in practice, the article concludes.

Gifts to Kim Jong Il from Russian Art Troupe 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the State Academy Beryozka Dancing Troupe of Russia Named after N. S. Nadezhdina on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was handed to an official concerned by its head Mira Koltsova. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gifts to him from the head and the manager of the troupe were also handed to the official concerned.

Indian Figure Denounces Japanese Authorities' Suppression of Chongryon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- J. K. Patel, director of the Indian Institute for Foreign Policy Studies, issued a statement on July 6, fully supporting the statement of a spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry denouncing the Japanese authorities for their crackdown upon the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a fact well-known all over the world that Chongryon is a legitimate organization of overseas citizens of the DPRK to protect the democratic national rights of the Koreans in Japan, the statement said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The acts of the Japanese authorities are a political fraud prompted by the sinister attempts to rob Chongryon of its base of activities and destroy Chongryon itself and, moreover, they are a blatant infringement upon the dignity and sovereignty of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We join the world people who love justice and conscience in bitterly denouncing the Japanese authorities' hostile policy toward the DPRK and Chongryon and demanding an immediate stop to their despicable suppression of Chongryon.

Abe Group's Suppression of Chongryon Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Wonsan, July 11 (KCNA) -- If the Abe group persists in ceaseless suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and Koreans in Japan, obsessed with foolish hallucination, it will meet a stern judgement by the Korean people aspiring after justice and peace and by history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Kwang Ung, vice-chairman of the Kangwon Provincial People's Committee, and representatives of workers, agricultural workers and youth and students warned this at the Wonsan mass meeting held on July 11 to condemn the Japanese reactionaries' suppression of Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Abe group has gone the lengths of moving to usurp the Hall of the Headquarters of Chongryon, having passed the limit in its dastardly and brutal moves to destroy Chongryon and the Korean community in Japan, the speakers noted, and went on: The Abe group is a team of reactionary gangsters putting into the shade the successive regimes of Japan in bitterness towards Koreans and moves against the DPRK and Chongryon. The hysteric racket of suppressing Chongryon and Koreans in Japan kicked off in the island country reminds one of the Japanese imperialists' barbarian repression of Koreans before liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such hysteric suppression of Chongryon once again discloses before the world the true colors of Japan as a barren land of democracy and humanitarianism and a state ill-famed for the worst human rights abuses and terrorism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Abe group's moves to do harm to Chongryon and Koreans in Japan are an unpardonable provocation to the DPRK and are nothing but self-destruction as they drive the DPRK-Japan relations to the worst ebb. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said sinister behavior of the Abe group bent on suppressing Chongryon without having even an iota of guilty conscience of the past is hardening the resolution of the Korean nation to certainly settle accounts with Japan, the sworn enemy, and mercilessly wipe out the bandits of Japanese militarism.

CRPP denuncia represion fascista de autoridades policiales de Seul
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 12 de julio (ATCC) -- Hace unos dias, las autoridades policiales metropolitanas de Seul apresaron y encarcelaron al jefe del departamento de la politica del comite de estudiantes del Partido de Obreros Democraticos acusandolo de haber violado la "ley de seguridad" al cometer el "crimen" de educar en la universidad la idea Juche a los estudiantes de grados inferiores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al respecto, el secretariado del Comite por la Reunificacion Pacifica de la Patria (CRPP) publico la vispera la informacion no. 932. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esa maniobra represiva resulta una conducta fascista que quiebra flagrantemente la aspiracion y el deseo de los habitantes y una accion anti-reunificacion y antinacional orientada a frenar la corriente de la epoca del 15 de Junio, senala el documento y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por su justeza y vigencia, hoy dia, la idea Juche y la politica de Songun (priorizacion militar) son apoyadas y aprobadas totalmente por la poblacion surcoreana y otros pueblos del mundo y estudiarlas y acatarlas deviene ya una infrenable corriente de la epoca. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al negar abiertamente la idea y el sistema de su contraparte del dialogo y fomentar la confrontacion fratricida justamente en esta epoca de "Entre nosotros, los connacionales", en que la nacion coreana marcha con sus fuerzas unidas hacia la reunificacion, las autoridades de seguridad publica cometen una brutal provocacion y desafio a la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y quiebran totalmente la base de las relaciones intercoreanas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Pero, de ninguna manera podran sofocar la aspiracion de las masas populares a defender la justicia y la verdad y a vivir con el patriotismo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Las autoridades surcoreanas de seguridad publica deberan ver correctamente tal aspiracion y la exigencia de la epoca y parar ahora mismo esa injusta represion a los adeptos a la idea Juche y la politica de Songun y la campana conflictiva con la RPDC.

Kim Yong Nam visitara Mongolia, Argelia y Etiopia
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 12 de julio (ATCC) -- El presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, Kim Yong Nam, realizara pronto una visita oficial y de amistad a Mongolia cumplimentando la invitacion del presidente de este pais, Nambariin Enkhbayar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Igualmente, hara una gira oficial y de amistad por la Republica Argelina Democratica y Popular y la Republica Federal Democratica de Etiopia.
